<br>
Vaal and Lileah nodded silently. Lileah didn’t want to give voice to the alternatives she saw in the prophecy.<br>
<br>
“Yes, Ianarae, that might be it.” Vaal said. Lileah could tell he wasn’t convinced of the truth of those words. “What do you make of it Emeroun? You seem to know it well.”<br>
<br>
